Sentencas: Herein, we present a heterostructure electrolyte with considerable potential for application in low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical energy conversion of solid oxide fuel cells through the interface effect in La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-8-BaTiO3-8 electrolyte

Sentencas: Heterostructure electrolytes are advantageous because the multiphase interfaces in their heterostructures are superior for ion conduction than for bulk conduc-tion.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical energy conversion of solid oxide fuel cells through the interface effect in La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-8-BaTiO3-8 electrolyte

Sentencas: Most previous studies on heterostructure electrolytes explained the influence of interfacial param-eters on ion conduction in terms of the space charge zones and lattice mismatch, neglecting the characterization of the interface.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical energy conversion of solid oxide fuel cells through the interface effect in La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-8-BaTiO3-8 electrolyte

Sentencas: In this study, a series of heterostructure electrolytes comprising La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-8 (LSCF) and BaTiO3-8 (BTO) with different composition ratios was developed.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical energy conversion of solid oxide fuel cells through the interface effect in La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-8-BaTiO3-8 electrolyte

Sentencas: Further, the lattice mismatch due to thermal stress in this system was evaluated by thermal expansion and electron energy loss spectroscopy (EELS) analyses.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical energy conversion of solid oxide fuel cells through the interface effect in La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-8-BaTiO3-8 electrolyte

Sentencas: Results indicated that 7LSCF-3BTO produced the narrowest interface and the most surface oxygen vacancies, suggesting that the stress generated by thermal expansion increased the density of the interface.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical energy conversion of solid oxide fuel cells through the interface effect in La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-8-BaTiO3-8 electrolyte

Sentencas: The cell with the optimal 7LSCF-3BTO com-position delivered a peak power density of 910 mW cm-2 and an open circuit voltage of 1.07 V at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical energy conversion of solid oxide fuel cells through the interface effect in La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-8-BaTiO3-8 electrolyte

Sentencas: The heterojunction effect was studied to elucidate the prevention of short circuiting in the LSCF-BTO cell, considering the Femi level and barrier energy height.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical energy conversion of solid oxide fuel cells through the interface effect in La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-8-BaTiO3-8 electrolyte

Sentencas: This study provides novel ideas for the design of electrolytes for LT-SOFCs from the interface perspective.(c) 2023
